  "prompt": "How do I know what he feels about me?",
  "response": "Understanding someone's feelings can be complex, but here are some tips to help you gauge how someone feels about you:\n\n### 1. **Pay Attention to Their Actions**  \n   - Actions often speak louder than words. Notice if they:  \n     - Make time for you consistently.  \n     - Show genuine interest in your life.  \n     - Go out of their way to help or support you.  \n\n### 2. **Listen to Their Words**  \n   - Do they express appreciation, admiration, or care for you?  \n   - Do they use phrases like \u201cI enjoy spending time with you\u201d or \u201cYou\u2019re important to me\u201d?  \n\n### 3. **Observe Their Body Language**  \n   - Positive signs include:  \n     - Maintaining eye contact.  \n     - Smiling or laughing around you.  \n     - Leaning in when talking to you.  \n     - Mirroring your gestures.  \n\n### 4. **Notice How They Treat You Compared to Others**  \n   - Do they give you special attention or prioritise you over others?  \n\n### 5. **Communicate Openly**  \n   - If you feel comfortable, have an honest conversation about your feelings and ask how they feel. Clear communication is key to understanding each other.  \n\n### 6. **Trust Your Intuition**  \n   - Your instincts can often sense whether someone cares for you or has deeper feelings.  \n\n### 7. **Look for Consistency**  \n   - Genuine feelings are usually consistent over time. If their behavior or attention fluctuates significantly, it might indicate uncertainty.  \n\nRemember, everyone expresses emotions differently, so patience and open communication are essential. If you\u2019re unsure, it\u2019s okay to ask them directly\u2014building trust and understanding is worth it!",
